  "texts": [
    "In contrast, in the field of human-computer interaction, human-like explanations are seen more favourably (de Graaf and Malle, 2017; Ehsan et al., 2019), indicating tension between the various goals and user groups of self-rationalising systems.",
    "The aim of this paper is to systematise properties of human explanations and to gauge to what extent these properties are reflected in the explanations generated by LLMs.",
    "This knowledge can help developers and users of these models understand in which cases the generated explanations are aligned with specific goals, and when a model needs to be adapted or is unfit for the intended use case.",
    "To get insights into the properties of LLM-generated explanations, we look into the Alpaca dataset (Taori et al., 2023; Peng et al., 2023).",
    "Choosing this dataset lets us study the properties of the explanations generated by GPT-4 (OpenAI, 2023), the LLM used in the construction of Alpaca."
  ],
